      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Applications <unitdate type="inclusive" normal="1952/1960">1952-1960</unitdate></unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The division of application forms into three series reflects the various filing arrangements practiced by the Subcommittee over time. There is very little actual overlap between the second and third series of applications, although the dates of coverage do overlap. The Applications (by Researcher) series is the earliest filing arrangement used by the Subcommittee and contains applications dating from 1952-1960. The second arrangement of Applications (by Radioisotope) covers the period 1961-1973 and contains files arranged alphabetically by abbreviations for the chemical element used in the research'. The researcher unfamiliar with these abbreviations should consult the table of elements included in this finding aid. This series includes an index file on 3 x 5 cards. Each card contains the researcher's name, project title, and chemical information for the isotope used. The third arrangement is found in the Applications (Chronological) series. This series covers the period 1954-1985, although the bulk of the files dates from 1970-1985. The application form required by the Subcommittee changed somewhat over the years covered by the three series, but taken together these three runs of applications provide a fairly comprehensive picture of radiation research involving human subjects from 1952 to the present. Each form provides basic information concerning the researcher, the research problem and strategy and the human Subjects.</p>
        </scopecontent>
