      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Officers' Files</unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The Officers' Files series is comprised of the files kept by Dr. Isadore Lampe, chairman of the Subcommittee from 1952-1962; by Dr. Charles S. Simons, a Subcommittee member from 1953. until circa 19701, and secretary from 1957 until his retirement; and by Dr. Ronald Bishop, a member from 1959-1985 and chairman from 1972-1935. Simons' files in particular include minutes of Subcommittee meetings, sometimes in draft form, although each of the other subseries does as well. Lampe's and Bishop's files contain materials from Radiation Control Service and the Radiation Policy Committee. Bishop was a member of the R.P.C. as well as of the Subcommittee, and the researcher will find in the Bishop subseries chronological files documenting R.P.C. activities from 1977-1985. The Officers' Files in general thus provide a broader Picture of radiation research and concerns at the University of Michigan, since they are less limited to activities involving human use. For example, it is here that 'the researcher will find the most information on growing concern with radio-active waste disposal and employee safety issues. However, the researcher should be prepared to use this series in conjunction with the first series, Chronological Files. Each contains similar materials, such as minutes, correspondence and reports.</p>
        </scopecontent>
